{"title":"Macworld Podcast: MacBook Neo, iPhone 17e, M5 Pro and M5 Max, and more new Apple products","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/3077229/macworld-podcast-macbook-neo-iphone-17e-m5-pro-and-m5-max-and-more-new-apple-products.html","date":1772756557000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com\">Macworld</a></p>\n\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>Are you experienced? This past week, Apple released the new iPhone 17e, M4 iPad Pro, new MacBooks, and more, and held its Apple Experience event. We’re covering it all on this episode of the Macworld Podcast. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is episode 973 with <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Michael-Simon/\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Simon</a>, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Jason-Cross/\" target=\"_blank\">Jason Cross</a>,  and <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Roman-Loyola/\" target=\"_blank\">Roman Loyola</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<h2>Watch episode 973 on YouTube</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<h2>Listen to episode 973 on Apple Podcasts</h2>\n\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t\n\t\t\t</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<h2>Listen to episode 973 on Spotify</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>New Apple products </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Click the links below for more information on the new products. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3073997\">Apple March event live blog</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3078150\">I met MacBook Neo. Everything I know is a lie</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3077864/apples-macbook-neo-is-599-whoa.html\">Apple’s MacBook Neo is $599? Whoa.</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3076654\">The MacBook Air has a new chip and a lower price (sort of)</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3075724\">The M5 Pro/Max MacBook Pros are a bigger upgrade than we thought</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3076520\">Apple’s MacBook pricing explained</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3076633\">Apple’s first mini-LED ProMotion monitor has a nice price</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3077141\">Your Mac might not work with the new Studio Displays </a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3075309\">The new iPad Air is basically the old iPad Air</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3075231\">Apple’s iPhone 17e gets MagSafe and A19, but it’s not all good news</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3078537/apple-has-one-more-release-this-week-os-26-3-1-is-here.html\">OS 26.3.1 is here</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>This Week in Apple History </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The very first Apple Studio Display was introduced on March 17, 1998, at the Seybold Seminars keynote in New York City. It was Apple’s first flat panel display, and Steve Jobs called it “very hot.” It was a 15-inch LCD with a maximum 1024 by 768 resolution, a 200 to 1 contrast ratio, and 180 nits of brightness. It came in a translucent blue case. Watch the introduction of the display below. </p>\n\n\n<div></div>\n\n\n<h2>Comment Corner </h2>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>It will be interesting to see what external display support is available with the new cheap MacBook with the “iPhone chip” and ports. I’m not expecting it to be good but am willing to be surprised. </p>\n<cite>Neil M. via email</cite></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>I could give a rats ass about anything to do with the new [entry-level] ipad EXCEPT if it has to use the dongle to charge the pencil. I have been on the verge of snapping that bastard in half many times over the pencil and that stupid, stupid dongle. I’m mad just typing this. </p>\n<cite>Phil V. via email</cite></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<h2>Subscribe to the Macworld Podcast</h2>\n